# Sliding Window in Java

The sliding window technique replaces a naive O(n²) nested loop with a single O(n) pass by maintaining a 'window' — a contiguous subarray or substring — and **sliding** it across the input. Instead of recomputing everything from scratch for each position, you add the new right element and remove the old left element, updating your answer incrementally.

## Fixed-size window — the moving frame
```java
// Problem: maximum sum of any k consecutive elements.
//
// Picture: a frame of width k sliding right one step at a time.
// [1  3  -1 | -3  5  3  6  7]   window sum = 3
//  [1  3  -1  -3 | 5  3  6  7]  slide: add 5, remove 1
//
int maxSumFixedWindow(int[] nums, int k) {
    int windowSum = 0, maxSum = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
    for (int r = 0; r < nums.length; r++) {
        windowSum += nums[r];                    // expand right
        if (r >= k) windowSum -= nums[r - k];   // shrink left (evict oldest)
        if (r >= k - 1) maxSum = Math.max(maxSum, windowSum);
    }
    return maxSum;
}
// Time: O(n)   Space: O(1)
```

## Variable-size window — the elastic frame
```java
// Problem: longest substring without repeating characters.
//
// The window EXPANDS right whenever possible.
// The window SHRINKS from the left whenever a constraint is violated.
//
// Picture hand holding a rubber band over the string:
//   a b c a b c b b
//   [a b c]            valid, expand
//   [a b c a]          'a' duplicate! shrink from left until valid
//     [b c a]          valid again, keep expanding
//
int lengthOfLongestSubstring(String s) {
    Map<Character, Integer> freq = new HashMap<>();
    int l = 0, maxLen = 0;
    for (int r = 0; r < s.length(); r++) {
        char c = s.charAt(r);
        freq.merge(c, 1, Integer::sum);           // add right char
        while (freq.get(c) > 1) {                 // constraint violated
            char leftChar = s.charAt(l++);
            freq.merge(leftChar, -1, Integer::sum); // shrink left
        }
        maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, r - l + 1);
    }
    return maxLen;
}
```

